page.title: 16CHILDS DAY AT WELLS, NORFOLK
page.content: I get up about 7.30 a.m. to go to school and put on my school uniform which is a grey skirt, blue shirt and blue jumper. For breakfast I have Frosties and a drink of lemonade. School lessons start at 9.10 a.m. but before I go to school I take my dog for a walk. At half past ten we have a 15 minute break and then stop for dinner at 11.55. In the afternoon school lasts from 1 to 3.30 p.m. After school I change into my jeans, then either play swingball with the lads next door or go to the shop for some groceries before 7 p.m. as it closes then. Before going to bed at 10 p.m. I watch T.V.
